---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="The policy gap ChipSettle addresses, and the project context behind it.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 space-y-8">
    <header>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">About ChipSettle</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">The policy gap</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        A semiconductor company deciding where to open an additional design site in Europe faces a
        documented problem: there is no single point where it can assemble the full picture of fiscal
        instruments, funding programs, visa pathways, and legal requirements across EU member states.
        The information exists — but it is scattered across national tax codes, EU regulations, and
        program websites that do not reference each other.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        A CFO who wants to weigh Germany's research allowance against the Netherlands' innovation box
        and expat ruling, while understanding how the EU's Chips Joint Undertaking and Pillar Two
        interact with both, currently has to reconstruct that picture from a dozen primary sources.
        ChipSettle assembles it into one verified, dated, filterable view.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">The approach</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        The tool is deliberately a structured navigator, not a chatbot. Every data point is traceable
        to a legal basis and an official source, with a verification date shown prominently. A
        deterministic decision engine filters the database to a company's profile; no answer is
        generated by a language model. For legal and fiscal information, traceability matters more than
        fluency.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        See the <a href="/methodology" class="text-blue-800 underline">methodology page</a> for how the
        engine filters and ranks, and how the database is verified and maintained.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Scope of v1</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        This first version focuses on the additional-design-site use case, with instruments seeded for
        Germany, the Netherlands, Belgium, France, Spain, and the EU level. It has no user accounts, no
        AI layer, and no automated data ingestion — every entry is manually verified. Future work may
        add email alerts when instruments in your profile change, an embeddable widget for economic
        development agencies, an API for site-selection tools, and multilingual support.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Source paper</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        The instrument dataset and the policy-gap analysis behind this tool are drawn from the
        underlying research on semiconductor design settlement policy in Europe. Instrument
        parameters are verified against official gazettes, tax authority publications, and program
        websites, each cited on the instrument's detail page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
      This tool provides structured policy information for orientation purposes only and does not
      constitute legal, tax, or investment advice.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
